column3: South Beach Road at  (Suburb:Brunswick Heads, Region:North Coast NSW)
column14: Avoid the area;
column15: Traffic Control will be in place. Please note: Access along South Beach Road will be restricted to South Beach Road and Lane residents, businesses and services during work hours, Monday to Friday. Limited parking will be made available along South Beach Rd on weekends. Torakina Carpark will be temporarily closed for periods of time during the construction period.On Monday 3rd February 2025, Council will start work on a major upgrade of South Beach Road, from the South Arm Bridge (including Torakina carpark) to the southern end of the road, adjacent to the Brunswick Heads Surf Club. South Beach Lane is not included in this stage. This $2.7m project includes:·        Resurfacing the road and carparking areas·        Drainage improvements and installation of kerb and gutter·        Placement of an asphalt wearing course layer·        Line marking and formalizing parking spaces The aim of the project is to improve traffic flow, maximize parking opportunities and enhance safety and connectivity for pedestrians and road users. The works are planned to be delivered in two stages, commencing in early February and completed in July 2025, weather permitting.  Stage 1 (early February to Easter 2025)·        Installation of new stormwater drainage, pavement widening and kerb and gutter installation. Stage 2 (May – July 2025)·        Road pavement construction works, including sealing and asphalt works, and landscaping.
